<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHARLES A. HELMERS; SAUGUS SCHOOLS OFFICIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Charles A. Helmers, who rose from student teacher to superintendent during a 
17-year career with the Saugus Union Elementary School District, has died of 
lung cancer. He was 41. 
</P>
<P>
Last November, Helmers looked on tearfully as district trustees named a new 
school in his honor during an emotion-filled ceremony. The Charles A. Helmers 
Elementary School is scheduled to open in 1990. 
</P>
<P>
Helmers, who died Wednesday, announced more than two years ago that he had 
inoperable lung cancer. He had not worked for about a year. 
</P>
<P>
Helmers, a Burbank resident, worked as a student teacher, teacher, principal 
and assistant superintendent before becoming district superintendent in 
December, 1985. He is survived by a sister, Beverly Speyer. 
</P>
<P>
Funeral services will be private. A memorial service will be held at 2 p.m. 
March 25 at Congregational Church of the Chimes in Sherman Oaks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
