<P>
WEEKEND TV SPORTS RUNDOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rain or shine, a field of nearly 20,000 runners will weather tough competition 
in the Los Angeles Marathon on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
For the fourth consecutive year, KCOP Channel 13 will carry the 26.2-mile race 
in a live, four-hour telecast. Pre-race coverage will begin at 8 a.m., with the 
event getting under way at 9 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Cable's USA Network will televise the marathon from noon to 3 p.m., and Channel 
13 will have an hourlong wrap-up at 6 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
From Florida comes the first of four Los Angeles Dodgers exhibition games on 
Sunday. The world champions will play the New York Mets at Vero Beach starting 
at 10:30 a.m. on Channel 11. 
</P>
<P>
Sunday also brings a pro basketball game between the Lakers and Houston Rockets 
at 12:30 p.m. (2). 
</P>
