 STRIKE VOTE PLANNED FOR GTE WORKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The union representing 15,000 hourly employees of GTE California said Friday it 
will take a strike vote against the telephone company next week. The union's 
contract with GTE was to expire tonight but has been temporarily extended until 
Tuesday at midnight. 
</P>
