team-high 23 points as Bel-Air Prep opened a 14-point lead midway through the 
fourth quarter in the Small Schools championship at Pepperdine. John Bahnsen of 
Newport Christian (21-3), who had been averaging 31 points in the playoffs, was 
held to 8 points in the first half, but finished with 27. By winning, Bel-Air 
Prep (20-8) qualified for the Southern California Regional tournament in 
Division V. Newport Christian, with a record of 21-3, has an excellent chance 
of qualifying as an at-large team. 
