</P>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
TITAN GYMNASTS GET RECORD-SETTING VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Fullerton women's gymnastics team set a school meet record for 
total score in a 192.25-186.45 victory over Auburn Friday in a nonconference 
meet at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
Gina Satterly and Stacey Harris of Fullerton tied for the overall title with a 
school-record 38.65. Satterly won the balance beam with a 9.75, and Harris won 
the uneven bars with a 9.75. Margot Gumerlock of Fullerton won the vault with a 
9.70, and teammate Lisa Dolan won the floor exercise with a 9.70. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference baseball: 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton 19, Portland 5 -- Fullerton (10-4) scored eight runs in the 
sixth to take a 15-4 lead at home. Huck Flenner (3-0) went six innings for the 
victory. Rex Peters had two doubles to stretch his hitting streak to 14 games. 
</P>
<P>
California 22, UC Irvine 5 -- UC Irvine starter Ken Whitworth, who had a line 
drive go off his pitching hand, had to leave the game in the first inning at 
Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
In the National Christian College Division II men's national basketball 
championships: 
</P>
<P>
Pacific Coast Christian 110, Bayridge 95 -- Steve Welch scored 24 points and 
Steve Heard had 18 for Pacific Coast Christian (32-9). 
</P>
<P>
In the National Christian College Athletic Assn. Division II women's basketball 
tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Northwest Assemblies of God 64, Pacific Coast Christian 56 -- Aiyanna Marcus 
scored 25 points for Northwest in a semifinal game. Donna Allen scored 22 
points for Pacific Coast Christian (19-12). 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference softball: 
</P>
<P>
Southern California 10-11, Pomona Pitzer 0-2 -- Lauren Kelly had two hits and 
scored two runs in the first game for host SCC. Christy George had three hits, 
two RBIs and scored a run in the second game for SCC (6-6). 
</P>
</TEXT>
