<HEADLINE>
<P>
55-ALIVE MATURE DRIVING CLASS SCHEDULE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Clipboard researched by Kathie Bozanich, Susan Davis Greene and Rick 
VanderKnyff / Los Angeles Times. Graphics by Doris Shields / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Since 1987, California licensed drivers 55 and older have been entitled to auto 
insurance premium discounts on liability, medical and collision coverage if 
every 3 years they take a state-approved course designed to improve driving 
skills and promote road safety. Although discounts depend on a driver's record 
and insurance carrier, the law applies to all California automobile insurance 
companies. 
</P>
<P>
The improvement course is available at private driving schools, public and 
private colleges and offered by nonprofit organizations at community-based 
locations. The cost is usually $8. The Department of Motor Vehicles will issue 
certificates to those who complete the course. The certificate must be 
submitted to an insurance carrier for discount benefit. 
</P>
<P>
Here is a list of places where classes will be held during March: 
</P>
<P>
Costa Mesa: March 8 and 9, 8:30 a.m.-12:30 p.m., at 1845 Park Ave. For more 
information call (714) 645-1032. 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach: March 13 and 14, 8:30 a.m.-12:30 p.m., at Huntington Beach 
Civic Center, 2000 Main St. (corner of Yorktown Avenue). For more information 
call (714) 536-9387. 
</P>
<P>
El Toro: March 10 and 11, 12:30 p.m.-4:30 p.m., at Freedom Village, 23442 El 
Toro Rd. For more information call Jan Snook at (714)768-1431. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine: March 9 and 10, 8 a.m.-noon, at the Irvine Senior Center, 3 Sandburg 
Way. For more information call (714)733-1055. 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Hills: March 20 and 21, 1 p.m.-5 p.m., at Laguna Hills Senior Citizens 
Center, 34210 Moulton Parkway (Willow Tree Center). For more information call 
Nancy at (714) 380-0155. Also March 7 and 8; March 14 and 15; March 28 and 29, 
each at 8 a.m.-noon, Leisure World, 23522 Paseo de Valencia. For more 
information call (714) 837-3550. 
</P>
<P>
San Clemente: March 7 and 8, 10 a.m.-2:30 p.m., at San Clemente Senior Citizen 
Center, 242 Avenida del Mar. For more information call Joan at (714) 498-3322. 
</P>
<P>
Seal Beach: March 30 and April 6, 8:30 a.m.-12:30 p.m. at 707 Electric Ave. For 
more information call (714) 828-8550 or (213) 431-2527. 
</P>
<P>
Source: American Association of Retired Persons 
</P>
</TEXT>
